adjectives.description: sculpted (comparative more sculpted, superlative most sculpted)

entries.meaning: Well shaped, as a good sculpture is.
examples: While cyclists often focus on crank-crushing quads or sculpted calves, all you have to do is realize, as Kita did, that the heart is not some mysterious, beating organ, but rather pure, powerhouse muscle.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of sculpt
